cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.MM

This paper is about video-based human action recognition, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep learning features, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper analyzes and compares different algorithms, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of Kinect camera, which is a human-computer interaction device, and could be classified under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the paper deals with benchmark datasets, which could be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia).
